  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Core Need**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on defining the core need: developing \"whisp,\" an anonymous, ephemeral social media app. It should offer a no-login experience, with posts vanishing within 24 hours. The focus is on a SvelteKit frontend to address this.\n\n\n**Adapting the Tech Stack**\n\nI\'ve hit some significant roadblocks. The AI Studio environment forces me to use React 18+ with Vite for the frontend, not SvelteKit as originally intended. Similarly, I must use an Express server for the backend, abandoning the Hono.js on Cloudflare Workers plan. Unfortunately, it seems that there is no Cloudflare D1 database available, so for MVP, I\'m going to have to use in-memory SQLite, or just an in-memory array.\n\n\n**Refining the Database Approach**\n\nI\'ve decided on in-memory SQLite (or simple file-based SQLite) for the Express backend. I\'m simulating Cloudflare KV with an in-memory Map or Redis. As for Cloudflare Cron, I\'ll use `setInterval` within the Express server for now. I\'m focusing on the UI/UX design: Monochrome theme (black and white) with a dark mode inversion toggle. The layout will be mobile-first and responsive using Tailwind CSS, featuring a linear feed with distinct \"Card\" post components. Each card will have a generated avatar color, anonymous author name, text content, up/down vote buttons, and an explicit countdown timer. I\'ve also defined the database schema for posts.\n\n\n**Detailing the Mechanics**\n\nI\'m now detailing the core mechanics. For anonymous identity, I will use HMAC-SHA256 based on IP or session ID. Name generation will use emojis, adjectives, and nouns. For interaction, up/down votes will use a KV store for rate limiting. The feed algorithm will calculate a gravity score for post ranking. I\'ll make sure to note the tech stack constraints: React, Express, and SQLite.\n\n\n**Implementing the Core**\n\nI\'m making progress implementing the frontend with React components for the feed, post card, and compose features. I\'ve integrated a dark mode toggle using Tailwind\'s `dark:` classes and React context. The next step is installing dependencies, updating scripts, and starting the Express server with SQLite database initialization. API endpoints will handle post creation (with token generation) and feed retrieval, sorted by a gravity score.\n\n\n**Finalizing the Components**\n\nI\'m now implementing the frontend logic, focusing on the `PostCard` and `ComposeForm` components in React. I\'m also adding timer functionality for post auto-deletion, displayed on the frontend and managed by the backend. The identity engine will use HMAC-SHA256 based on IP, a secret salt, and the current date, with lists of adjectives, nouns, and emojis for name generation. For the feed, I\'ll sort posts in JavaScript, since SQLite\'s `POW()` might be an issue, or the database is small.\n\n\n**Calculating the Score**\n\nI\'m now focusing on calculating the score and installing dependencies. The formula will be `Score = (UP - DOWN) / ((Age in Hours) + 2)^1.8`. I\'m installing `better-sqlite3`, `@types/better-sqlite3`, `clsx`, and `tailwind-merge` for styling. My next step is drafting `server.ts`.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 19
      nanos: 920003882
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
