    modified_response: "I have successfully built the Minimum Viable Product for **whisp.**\n\nSince this web application needed to run within the AI Studio container environment instead of Cloudflare, I have implemented an architecture aligned exactly with your requested feature mechanics: transitioning Cloudflare Workers and D1 to a robust **Express server with an in-memory SQLite (`better-sqlite3`) edge database**, while preserving every core mechanic requested.\n\nHere is a breakdown of the implementation:\n\n- **Monochrome Minimalist UI**: The platform defaults to a crisp, high-contrast black-and-white theme using Tailwind CSS, including a user-toggled manual dark mode inversion switch. \n- **Babel Identity Engine**: Implemented deterministic user identities via HMAC-SHA256(IP + Date + Salt). It seamlessly pairs Emojis with categorized Adjectives and Nouns translated natively across different scripts, and utilizes the first 6 hex characters of the token to generate strict user color codes for styling. I\'ve also utilized the `<bdi>` tag to inherently shield Arabic and other RTL languages from breaking formatting directionalities.\n- **Dynamic Gravity Feed**: The Express server successfully sorts all valid posts purely algorithmically using your custom gravity constant score formula ($G = 1.8$).\n- **Interaction Engine & KV Emulation**: Posts can be voted UP (boosting visibility) or DOWN. To mimic the Cloudflare KV limits, the server retains a 24-hour synchronized memory hash (`interact:postID:authorToken`) to permanently block multiple spam responses from identical tokens, and actively shields feeds by auto-hiding any posts that meet the `-5` score differential threshold.\n- **Ephemeral Automation**: Real-time interval systems clear posts older than exactly 24 hours autonomously, matched by the precise, minute-ticking timers shown to end-users inside each card (e.g., *\"Disappears in 20h 5m\"*)."
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 875137757
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
steps {
  type: CORTEX_STEP_TYPE_USER_INPUT
  status: CORTEX_STEP_STATUS_DONE
  metadata {
    created_at {
      seconds: 1780479185
      nanos: 342107975
    }
    source: CORTEX_STEP_SOURCE_USER_EXPLICIT
  }
  user_input {
    user_response: "SYSTEM ROLE & PROJECT OBJECTIVEAct as a Senior Full-Stack Software Engineer and UI/UX Expert. Your task is to develop a complete, production-ready Minimum Viable Product (MVP) web application named \"whisp\".\nIt is a 100% anonymous, zero-login, and ephemeral global social media platform where all posts automatically delete after 24 hours.1. INFRASTRUCTURE & TECH STACKMust strictly use the Cloudflare free-tier ecosystem:Frontend & SSR: SvelteKit deployed on Cloudflare Pages. Use Tailwind CSS for all styling.Backend/API Router: Hono.js running on Cloudflare Workers.Primary Database: Cloudflare D1 (SQLite at the edge) for structured post data.Caching & State: Cloudflare KV for IP rate-limiting and preventing interaction spam.Cron Jobs: Cloudflare Cron Workers scheduled every hour to execute DELETE FROM posts WHERE expires_at < CURRENT_TIMESTAMP.2. DATABASE SCHEMA (Cloudflare D1)Create a single table named posts. Execute this schema:id: String (Primary Key, 8-character Nanoid).content: Text (Max 500 characters).author_name: String (Babel identity output).author_token: String (HMAC IP hash).up_count: Integer (Default 0).down_count: Integer (Default 0).created_at: Timestamp (Default CURRENT_TIMESTAMP).expires_at: Timestamp (created_at + 24 hours).reply_to: String (Nullable, references posts.id).3. CORE BACKEND LOGICA. The \"Babel\" Identity Engine (Strictly Stateless)Do not store user IPs. Generate a daily identity via backend API logic before inserting a post:Generate Token:$$\\text{Token Unik} = \\text{HMAC-SHA256}(\\text{IP Public} + \\text{Secret Salt} + \\text{Tanggal Hari Ini})$$Name Mapping: Use the token to deterministically index into in-memory arrays to select: [1 Emoji] + [1 Adjective] + [1 Noun]. Use 10 mixed native scripts (e.g., Cyrillic, Hanzi, Arabic, Hangul, Latin).Avatar Color: Extract the first 6 hex characters of the Token to generate a valid hex color code (e.g., #FF5733).B. Interaction & Moderation (UP/DOWN)Spam Prevention: When an IP interacts, write interact:{postID}:{authorToken} to Cloudflare KV. If it exists, return HTTP 403.Auto-Hide Moderation: If up_count - down_count <= -5, immediately flag the post in the API response to be hidden from the UI.C. Feed AlgorithmSort the main feed using this exact SQL formula:\n$$\\text{Score} = \\frac{\\text{UP} - \\text{DOWN}}{(\\text{Age in Hours} + 2)^G}$$Set G = 1.8. Sort results ORDER BY Score DESC.4. GLOBAL UI/UX DESIGN SYSTEM (TAILWIND CSS)Theme: Strict Monochrome (Black & White). Absolutely no colors except for the dynamically generated author_color for avatars.Dark Mode: Implement dark: variants in Tailwind for a full UI inversion (White text on Deep Black #0a0a0a background).Typography: Use a clean, neutral sans-serif font (e.g., Inter or system-ui).Layout: Mobile-first, single-column linear feed centered on the screen. Max container width: max-w-xl (512px).5. COMPONENT-LEVEL REQUIREMENTS (PIXEL PERFECT)A. HeaderSticky top, frosted glass effect (backdrop-blur-md, bg-white/80, dark: bg-black/80).Title: \"whisp\" (lowercase, bold, mono font).Button: A simple, prominent \"New Post\" floating action button (FAB) or header button.B. Post Card Component (Crucial)Render each post as a distinct \"Card\" (border, border-gray-200, dark:border-gray-800, rounded-xl, p-4, mb-4, shadow-sm).Header of Card: * Avatar: A circle (w-8 h-8 rounded-full) filled with the generated author_color hex.Name: The Babel identity. MUST be wrapped in <bdi> tags to isolate RTL/LTR rendering (e.g., <bdi>\360\237\246\212</bdi> <bdi>C\320\274\320\265\321\210\320\275\320\276\320\271</bdi> <bdi>Gato</bdi>).FOMO Timer: Positioned top right. Text: \"Disappears in Xh Xm\" (Dynamically calculated based on expires_at). Use a mono font, text-xs, text-gray-500.Body of Card:The content text. Break words properly.Footer of Card (Actions): * UP Button: An upward arrow icon + up_count. Pressing it triggers the UP API endpoint.DOWN Button: A downward arrow icon. Pressing it triggers the DOWN API endpoint.Reply Button: A comment icon to open a modal setting reply_to = post.id.SHARE BUTTON: (See Section 6).6. VIRAL SHARE FEATURE IMPLEMENTATION (THE \"SHARE CARD\")This is a mandatory growth vector.UI: Add a \"Share\" icon button in the Post Card footer.Action Logic: When clicked, use a frontend library like html2canvas or the native Web Share API (if supported).The Exportable Canvas: Create a hidden or visually pristine clone of the Post Card component specifically for exporting.It must contain the Avatar, the Babel Name, the Content, and a watermark at the bottom reading \"whispered on whisp\".It must have a solid background (white or black depending on the active theme) to ensure screenshots render perfectly in WhatsApp/Instagram stories.Output: Trigger a download of the .png image or open the native OS sharing sheet with the image blob attached."
    items {
      text: "SYSTEM ROLE & PROJECT OBJECTIVEAct as a Senior Full-Stack Software Engineer and UI/UX Expert. Your task is to develop a complete, production-ready Minimum Viable Product (MVP) web application named \"whisp\".\nIt is a 100% anonymous, zero-login, and ephemeral global social media platform where all posts automatically delete after 24 hours.1. INFRASTRUCTURE & TECH STACKMust strictly use the Cloudflare free-tier ecosystem:Frontend & SSR: SvelteKit deployed on Cloudflare Pages. Use Tailwind CSS for all styling.Backend/API Router: Hono.js running on Cloudflare Workers.Primary Database: Cloudflare D1 (SQLite at the edge) for structured post data.Caching & State: Cloudflare KV for IP rate-limiting and preventing interaction spam.Cron Jobs: Cloudflare Cron Workers scheduled every hour to execute DELETE FROM posts WHERE expires_at < CURRENT_TIMESTAMP.2. DATABASE SCHEMA (Cloudflare D1)Create a single table named posts. Execute this schema:id: String (Primary Key, 8-character Nanoid).content: Text (Max 500 characters).author_name: String (Babel identity output).author_token: String (HMAC IP hash).up_count: Integer (Default 0).down_count: Integer (Default 0).created_at: Timestamp (Default CURRENT_TIMESTAMP).expires_at: Timestamp (created_at + 24 hours).reply_to: String (Nullable, references posts.id).3. CORE BACKEND LOGICA. The \"Babel\" Identity Engine (Strictly Stateless)Do not store user IPs. Generate a daily identity via backend API logic before inserting a post:Generate Token:$$\\text{Token Unik} = \\text{HMAC-SHA256}(\\text{IP Public} + \\text{Secret Salt} + \\text{Tanggal Hari Ini})$$Name Mapping: Use the token to deterministically index into in-memory arrays to select: [1 Emoji] + [1 Adjective] + [1 Noun]. Use 10 mixed native scripts (e.g., Cyrillic, Hanzi, Arabic, Hangul, Latin).Avatar Color: Extract the first 6 hex characters of the Token to generate a valid hex color code (e.g., #FF5733).B. Interaction & Moderation (UP/DOWN)Spam Prevention: When an IP interacts, write interact:{postID}:{authorToken} to Cloudflare KV. If it exists, return HTTP 403.Auto-Hide Moderation: If up_count - down_count <= -5, immediately flag the post in the API response to be hidden from the UI.C. Feed AlgorithmSort the main feed using this exact SQL formula:\n$$\\text{Score} = \\frac{\\text{UP} - \\text{DOWN}}{(\\text{Age in Hours} + 2)^G}$$Set G = 1.8. Sort results ORDER BY Score DESC.4. GLOBAL UI/UX DESIGN SYSTEM (TAILWIND CSS)Theme: Strict Monochrome (Black & White). Absolutely no colors except for the dynamically generated author_color for avatars.Dark Mode: Implement dark: variants in Tailwind for a full UI inversion (White text on Deep Black #0a0a0a background).Typography: Use a clean, neutral sans-serif font (e.g., Inter or system-ui).Layout: Mobile-first, single-column linear feed centered on the screen. Max container width: max-w-xl (512px).5. COMPONENT-LEVEL REQUIREMENTS (PIXEL PERFECT)A. HeaderSticky top, frosted glass effect (backdrop-blur-md, bg-white/80, dark: bg-black/80).Title: \"whisp\" (lowercase, bold, mono font).Button: A simple, prominent \"New Post\" floating action button (FAB) or header button.B. Post Card Component (Crucial)Render each post as a distinct \"Card\" (border, border-gray-200, dark:border-gray-800, rounded-xl, p-4, mb-4, shadow-sm).Header of Card: * Avatar: A circle (w-8 h-8 rounded-full) filled with the generated author_color hex.Name: The Babel identity. MUST be wrapped in <bdi> tags to isolate RTL/LTR rendering (e.g., <bdi>\360\237\246\212</bdi> <bdi>C\320\274\320\265\321\210\320\275\320\276\320\271</bdi> <bdi>Gato</bdi>).FOMO Timer: Positioned top right. Text: \"Disappears in Xh Xm\" (Dynamically calculated based on expires_at). Use a mono font, text-xs, text-gray-500.Body of Card:The content text. Break words properly.Footer of Card (Actions): * UP Button: An upward arrow icon + up_count. Pressing it triggers the UP API endpoint.DOWN Button: A downward arrow icon. Pressing it triggers the DOWN API endpoint.Reply Button: A comment icon to open a modal setting reply_to = post.id.SHARE BUTTON: (See Section 6).6. VIRAL SHARE FEATURE IMPLEMENTATION (THE \"SHARE CARD\")This is a mandatory growth vector.UI: Add a \"Share\" icon button in the Post Card footer.Action Logic: When clicked, use a frontend library like html2canvas or the native Web Share API (if supported).The Exportable Canvas: Create a hidden or visually pristine clone of the Post Card component specifically for exporting.It must contain the Avatar, the Babel Name, the Content, and a watermark at the bottom reading \"whispered on whisp\".It must have a solid background (white or black depending on the active theme) to ensure screenshots render perfectly in WhatsApp/Instagram stories.Output: Trigger a download of the .png image or open the native OS sharing sheet with the image blob attached."
    }
  }
}
