  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing the Error Source**\n\nI\'ve traced the \"oklab\" color function error in the share feature directly to `html2canvas`\'s incompatibility with Tailwind CSS v3\'s color generation. It seems this library doesn\'t support the newer CSS color spaces. My focus is now on workarounds and solutions, assessing options like upgrading `html2canvas` or finding an alternative approach to generating the screenshot.\n\n\n**Evaluating Color Function Conflicts**\n\nI\'m now investigating specific strategies for resolving the `html2canvas` color compatibility issue within the `ShareCanvas` component. I\'m leaning toward explicitly defining RGB/Hex color values on the component\'s elements to avoid `html2canvas` misinterpreting Tailwind\'s `oklab` or `oklch` outputs. However, I need to check if Tailwind v4 could natively output hex colors for default tokens, such as `bg-white`, so I am also considering that possibility.\n\n\n**Switching to New Rendering Tool**\n\nI\'ve determined that the `oklab` and `oklch` color function issue within `html2canvas` stems from its incompatibility with Tailwind v4\'s default color outputs. The primary colors in this case are being interpreted, and the error persists. Rather than continue with workarounds that introduce additional complexity, I am pivoting to the `html-to-image` package. This approach seems far superior for handling modern CSS.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 163546165
    }
